# Skills Directory Structure

## Current Structure (Skills CLI Format)

```
skills/
├── .structure                           # This file - explains the layout
├── README.md                            # User-facing documentation
├── skills.json                          # Source manifest (used by conversion script)
│
├── bem-naming/
│   └── SKILL.md                        # BEM methodology skill
├── component-composition/
│   └── SKILL.md                        # Component composition patterns
├── component-guidance-actions/
│   └── SKILL.md                        # Actions & controls (4 components)
├── component-guidance-data/
│   └── SKILL.md                        # Data display (23 components)
├── component-guidance-feedback/
│   └── SKILL.md                        # Feedback & status (15 components)
├── component-guidance-forms/
│   └── SKILL.md                        # Forms & inputs (26 components)
├── component-guidance-layout/
│   └── SKILL.md                        # Layout & containers (11 components)
├── component-guidance-navigation/
│   └── SKILL.md                        # Navigation (8 components)
├── content-density/
│   └── SKILL.md                        # Cozy/compact/condensed modes
└── layout-patterns/
    └── SKILL.md                        # Complete page patterns
```

## SKILL.md Format

Each `SKILL.md` file has YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
name: bem-naming                         # Matches folder name (required)
description: BEM methodology guide...    # Brief description (required)
user-invocable: false                    # Auto-loaded, not manually invoked
metadata:                                # Custom metadata (optional)
  tags: ["bem", "naming", "css"]
  keywords: ["block-element-modifier"]
---

# Skill Content Here
```

## Installation by External Applications

```bash
npx skills add SAP/fundamental-styles
```

Installs to: `.claude/skills/fundamental-styles/{skill-id}/SKILL.md`
